data.description: RECENTLY RENOVATED AND READY TO MOVE IN THIS CLASSIC RESIDENCE AWAITS YOU.  NESTLED IN AN ESTABLISHED QUIET, SECLUDED, TREE LINED NEIGHBORHOOD, AMONGST SINGLE FAMILY HOMES, AND ONLY MINUTES AWAY FROM SOME OF THE FINEST WHITE SAND BEACHES WITH STUNNING SUNSETS, AND NEAR TO MANHATTAN BEACH PIER, HOME OF THE MANHATTAN BEACH OPEN VOLLEYBALL TOURNAMENT. CURRENTLY A 2 BEDROOM WITH CONVERTIBLE DEN HOME THAT CAN EASILY BE CONVERTED BACK TO A 3 BEDROOM LOCATED IN NORTH REDONDO BEACH WITHIN THE TRW TRACT. ENTER THIS TURN-KEY HOME WITH GLEAMING REFINISHED HARDWOOD FLOORS INTO AN OPEN AND SPACIOUS COMBINDED LIVING/DINING ROOM WITH A LARGE GAS/WOOD FIREPLACE AND PICTURESQUE BAY WINDOW. ALL SOLID NATURAL WOOD THROUGHOUT INCLUDING INTERIOR DOORS AND BEAM. LIGHT FILLED KITCHEN WITH GRANITE COUNTERS AND A BREAKFAST EATING AREA SURROUNDED BY FILTERED SUNLIGHT COMING THROUGH THE LARGEWINDOW AND SLIDING DOORS LEADING TO A BACK PATIO. MAIN BEDROOM HAS ENSUITE BATHROOM WITH WALK-IN TILED SHOWER AND GRANITE SINKCOUNTER, SECONDARY BEDROOM HAS NICE DEEP OVERSIZED JACUZZZI TUB/SHOWER COMBO. SETTLE INTO THE BACKYARD TO ENJOY A NICE QUIET, SERENE, SETTING WITH MATURE TREES AND 2 UNITS FOR EXTRA STORAGE. A SECOND PATIO OFF THE BACKYARD LEADS TO A TWO-CAR GARAGE. AMPLE PARKING; AS THIS HOME ACCOMMODATES 3-4 CARS IN A LONG DRIVEWAY. A "MUST SEE" HOME IN A GREAT NEIGHBORHOOD WITH GREAT SCHOOLS NEARBY, CLOSE TO RESTAURANTS, MANHATTAN BEACH MALL, AND EVERYTHING THE SOUTH BAY HAS TO OFFER.
